        <headline>Extreme Heat Watch issued July 6 at 1:16AM MST until July 9 at 8:00PM MST by NWS Flagstaff AZ</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Dangerously hot conditions, with temperatures up to 112
possible below 4000 feet.

* WHERE...Northern Gila County and Yavapai County Valleys and Basins.

* WHEN...From Wednesday morning through Wednesday evening.

* IMPACTS...Most individuals will be at risk for heat-related
illnesses without effective cooling or adequate hydration,
especially with prolonged outdoor exposure.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.

Do not leave young children and pets in unattended vehicles. Car
interiors will reach lethal temperatures in a matter of minutes.

Take extra precautions when outside. Wear lightweight and loose
fitting clothing. Try to limit strenuous activities to early morning
or evening.</instruction>
